other_tests.findings: The imaged lung bases are clear. There is no pleural effusion. Heart size is normal without pericardial effusion. The liver shows homogeneous enhancement without focal lesions. No evidence of intrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. The gallbladder is incompletely distended with no wall edema or pericholecystic fluid collection. No calcified gallstones are seen. The spleen is unremarkable, and the pancreas enhances homogeneously without ductal dilatation. Adrenal glands are normal, and kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically without hydronephrosis. Bowel loops are normal in caliber without evidence of thickening or obstruction. Proximal appendix is normal and air-filled. Appendiceal tip appears bulbous measuring up to 8 mm with mild adjacent fat stranding. The bladder, distal ureters, rectum, uterus, and sigmoid colon are unremarkable. There is a 2.3 x 3 cm right adnexal cyst. No free air or free fluid in the pelvis. No pathologically enlarged lymph nodes.
